{
  "texts": [
    "Efficiency gains, as seen in radiology (Huang et al., 2025), may carry over to SLP, reducing administrative workload and enabling faster intervention.",
    "However, AI tools must undergo rigorous validation before widespread clinical use, even if risks are relatively low (Kissinger et al., 2022).",
    "As AI agents gain autonomy, their role in extending screening into assessment will require strict clinician oversight and vigilant ethical safeguards.",
    "SLPs develop and deliver individualized and group treatment plans targeting communication and swallowing disorders.",
    "AI can complement these efforts through personalized apps, adaptive learning platforms, and virtual practice environments, delivering real-time feedback, tracking progress, and enhancing accessibility."
  ]
}